The preacher's specific request—"I urge you the more earnestly to do 
this in order that I may be restored to you the sooner" (v. 19)—reflects his 
simple faith in prayer. If they fail to pray, his return to them may be slowed or 
possibly never take place. But if they pray, he expects that their prayers will 
speed his restoration, just as Daniel's prayers brought the return of the angel 
Gabriel to aid him (cf. Daniel 10:12–14). He believed in prayer!
